name: "Stainedglassman" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Felt pen on reclaimed cardboard with digital embellishments and color.] A stained glass image of the unholy beast. Some say, when the coven is in its hour of deepest need, the very glass itself can come to life and do the sisters' will... ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
